SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1273
By Roberts
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Elijah Kannel, 2026
Salutatorian of Innovation Academy.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Elijah Kannel is one such exceptional student, who was recently named
Salutatorian of the 2026 graduating class at Innovation Academy; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Mr. Kannel has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in his remarkable high school career, Elijah Kannel has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in a number of extracurricular activities; and
WHEREAS, his display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well for his
future success; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Kannel's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for
his family, his school, and his community; and
WHEREAS, Elijah Kannel's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and honor the 2026 Innovation
